{{Infobox person |image = Nancy Walls @ 2010 Academy Awards.jpg |imagesize = |caption = Carell at the [[82nd Academy Awards|2010 Academy Awards]] | name = Nancy Carell | birth_name = Nancy Ellen Walls | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1966|07|19}} | birth_place = [[Cohasset, Massachusetts]], U.S. | other_names = Nancy Walls | residence = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]], U.S. | alma mater = [[Boston College]] | occupation = {{flatlist| *Actress *Comedian *Writer}} | years_active = 1995–present | spouse = {{marriage|[[Steve Carell]]|August 5, 1995}} | children = 2 }}
'''Nancy Ellen Carell''' ({{IPAc-en|k|ə|ˈ|r|ɛ|l}}; née '''Walls'''; born July 19, 1966) is an American actress, comedian and writer best known for her work on ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'', ''[[The Daily Show]]'' and ''[[The Office (U.S. TV series)|The Office]]''. In 2016, she co-created the [[TBS (U.S. TV channel)|TBS]] comedy series ''[[Angie Tribeca]]'' with her husband, [[Steve Carell]].
==Early life== Carell was born and raised in [[Cohasset, Massachusetts]]. She attended [[Boston College]] where she graduated in 1988. While a student at BC, she was a member of the improvisational troupe "My Mother's Fleabag."<ref>{{cite web|last1=Wright|first1=Megh|title=Saturday Night's Children: Nancy Walls (1995-1996)|url=http://splitsider.com/2012/04/saturday-nights-children-nancy-walls-1995-1996/|website=SplitSider|publisher=The Awl|accessdate=6 November 2014}}</ref>
==Career== Carell got her start in comedy at [[The Second City]] in [[Chicago]] and, like many of the troupe's alumni, went on to join the cast of ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'' (1995–96), where she was best known for her [[Impressionist (entertainment)|impression]] of [[CNN]] [[News presenter|anchor]] [[Bobbie Battista]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Nancy Carell Biography|url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/celebrity/nancy_carell/biography|publisher=rotten tomatoes|accessdate=22 August 2015}}</ref> She later held a correspondent position on the satirical [[News program|TV news]] program ''[[The Daily Show]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Definitive Ranking of All of the Daily Show Correspondents|url=http://www.vh1.com/news/45507/daily-show-correspondents-ranked/|publisher=vh1|accessdate=22 August 2015}}</ref> She voiced the character of Helen Goode on the [[Mike Judge]]-created animated series ''[[The Goode Family]]'' on [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]],<ref>{{cite web|title=The Goode Family|url=http://www.foxnews.com/photoessay/0,4644,7337,00.html/#/photoessay/image/0527091440_M_goode1_450-jpg|publisher=Fox news|accessdate=22 August 2015}}</ref> where she was credited for the first time as Nancy Carell instead of Nancy Walls. Carell occasionally guest-starred on ''[[The Office (U.S. TV series)|The Office]]'', which starred her husband [[Steve Carell]] until 2011, as [[List of characters from The Office (US TV series)#Carole Stills|Carole Stills]], a [[Real estate broker|real estate agent]] and former girlfriend of her husband's character, [[Michael Scott (The Office)|Michael Scott]]. She also had a brief appearance in the movie ''[[Bridesmaids (2011 film)|Bridesmaids]]''.<ref>{{cite news|title=Who is Steve Carell's Wife? Nancy Carell Looks Familiar for Good Reason|url=http://www.bustle.com/articles/57343-who-is-steve-carells-wife-nancy-carell-looks-familiar-for-good-reason|accessdate=22 August 2015|publisher=bustle.com}}</ref>
Carell and her husband [[Steve Carell|Steve]] created the [[TBS (U.S. TV channel)|TBS]] comedy series ''[[Angie Tribeca]]'' starring [[Rashida Jones]]. The series premiered on January 17, 2016.
==Personal life== Carell is married to actor-comedian [[Steve Carell]], whom she met when she was a student in an [[improvisation]] class he was teaching at [[The Second City Training Center|Second City]].<ref>''[[The Tonight Show with Jay Leno]]'', (January 11, 2006). [[NBC]].</ref> They have two children: daughter Elisabeth (born in 2001) and son John (born in 2004).<ref>{{cite web|title=Nancy and Steve Carell Marriage Profile|url=http://marriage.about.com/od/entertainmen1/p/stevecarell.htm|publisher=[[About.com]]|accessdate=22 August 2015}}</ref>
==Filmography== * ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'' as Herself/Various (1995–1996) (20 episodes) * ''[[The Daily Show]]'' as Correspondent (1999–2002) (90 episodes) * ''[[Anger Management (film)|Anger Management]]'' as Flight Attendant (2003) <ref name="films"/> * ''[[The 40-Year-Old Virgin]]'' as Health Clinic Counselor (2005)<ref>{{cite web|title=40-Year-Old Virgin' turns 10: Watch 6 of Steve Carell's funniest film clips|url=http://www.today.com/parents/taylor-swift-dedicates-ronan-performance-mom-whose-son-died-cancer-t39626|publisher=Today.com|accessdate=22 August 2015}}</ref> * ''[[The Office (U.S. TV series)|The Office]]'' as Carol Stills (2005–2006, 2010, 2013) (7 episodes) * ''[[The Goode Family]]'' as Helen Goode (2009) (13 episodes) * ''[[Bridesmaids (2011 film)|Bridesmaids]]'' as Helen's tennis partner (2011) * ''[[Seeking a Friend for the End of the World]]'' as Linda Petersen (2012)<ref name="films">{{cite web|title=Nancy Carrel profile|url=http://www.metacritic.com/person/nancy-carell?filter-options=movies|publisher=[[metacritic]]|accessdate=22 August 2015}}</ref> * ''[[Angie Tribeca]]'' (2017) as Katy Perry (2 episodes)
